attributes.Long form description: The student grabs the lever. The instructor asks the student slide the shift arm onto the mounting peg. The student grabs the arm of the motorcycle and holds the shift arm. The student approach to the mounting peg, attaches the shift arm to the pe and presses it. Approach the parts bin and grabs a bolt, insert the bolt in the washer, and attach it to the peg. Screw the bolt, then approach the tool car to grab the ratcher, insert it in the peg, and tighten the bolt. Puts the ratchet on the tool car. Then grabs the lever to change the positions, grabs the remote, presses the down button and presses it to the up, and puts the remote in the motorcycle base. The student grabs the lever to put it in a neutral position, grabs the ratchet and holds the ratcher adjuster, attaches the ratcher to the bolt, and unscrews it. Drops the bolt and the washer, put the bolt on the motorcycle base and the in the parts bin. The student grabs the arm and removes the mounting peg.
